          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Samuel 28:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 31:10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. The iniquities themselves. This phrase cannot be understood of Christ. For although our sins are said to be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "laid upon Christ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Isaiah 53",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and upon that account he is said to be made sin for us, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 5:21",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Corinthians 5:21",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; yet the Scripture every where represents him as one that never knew nor did any sin, as in that place, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Peter 2:22",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Peter 2:22",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and elsewhere; and even when his punishment is described, yet it is expressly noted, that he did not suffer for himself, or for his own sins, but only for us, and for our sins, as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Isaiah 53:4,5 Da 9:26 1 Peter 2:24",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 53:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",5 Da 9:26 ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Peter 2:24",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". And therefore it is not probable that the Holy Ghost would use such an expression concerning the sinless Christ of God, as is never used in Scripture, but either of a man’s own sins, or of the punishment deserved by his own sins. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Have taken hold upon me:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " men’s sins are figuratively said to follow them, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Timothy 5:24",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Timothy 5:24",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and to find them out, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Numbers 32:23",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 32:23",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and here ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to take hold of them",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as a serjeant takes hold of a man whom he arrests. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
